3.00	1984_James_Hardie_1000	1984 James Hardie 1000	The 1984 James Hardie 1000 was the 25th running of the Bathurst 1000 touring car race. It was held on 30 September 1984 at the Mount Panorama Circuit just outside Bathurst in New South Wales, Australia and was Round 4 of the 1984 Australian Endurance Championship. This race was celebrated as 'The Last of the Big Bangers', in reference to the Group C touring cars, which were competing at Bathurst for the last time.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Brock-vk.jpg/220px-Brock-vk.jpg
